title: Man Suspected Of Shooting 3 Dead In NSW Was Out On Bail For DV Charges | 10 News+
description: It has been revealed today that Julian Ingram, the man suspected of shooting dead three people in Lake Cargelligo - including his pregnant former partner - was in the community on bail for domestic violence charges. A massive manhunt is now underway in regional New South Wales for the 37-year-old, with more than 100 police officers on the ground hunting for him. title: Boxer Turned Rapper Anthony Mundine’s New Song Ft. Archie Rose | 10 News+

title: South-East Australia Heatwave Sparks Catastrophic Fire Danger | 10 News
description: Millions of Aussies across the south-east are sweltering through a scorching heatwave, with relief still well away for some. The rising mercury playing havoc on major sporting events, forcing disruptions at the Australian Open tennis and cycling’s Tour Down Under. Temperatures have soared well past 40 in parts of Victoria and South Australia, sparking catastrophic fire danger in some parts, and authorities warn it could be just the beginning. title: Lake Cargelligo Shooting: Police Expand Search For Suspected Triple Murderer | 10 News
description: An already extensive search area has expanded even further in New South Wales’ Central West for a triple murderer. Julian Ingram was on bail for DV charges when he was accused of shooting dead three people, including his pregnant former partner. Tonight, police are refusing to reveal too much about just where they are looking, but are not ruling out the possibility that someone, somewhere, is helping him hide.
